Galaxy Cruise - Halong Bay
Jul 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
My wife and I have just returned from the two night/three day cruise on the Galaxy Cruise boat in Halong Bay.
There are a lot of cruise companies and we chose this because of previous comments on tripadvisor.
We were picked up from our hotel in a very modern bus with good aircon and comfortable seating. The drive out was typical Vietnamese style but we felt very safe.
The boat looked quite old (they all did!) but our room had modern amenities and was extremely clean with clean linen and aircon worked fine. There was a good fridge; it‚Äôs worth saying that some people we spoke to (from other boats) said their rooms didn‚Äôt have a fridge. There was no safe, but the rooms were lockable.
There was way too much food to eat. Mostly seafood based and cooked lovely with garnish that was very impressive.
All of the staff were excellent, they were cheerful, and tried to assist whenever they could. We had two tour guides, Dwon and Hoan (not sure about the spelling); Hoan‚Äôs nickname is ‚Äòhappy‚Äô. They were fantastic, both very lovely people, they were very cheerful and tried to assist wherever possible. We heard some awful stories of tour guides and staff on other boats but I can‚Äôt praise ours enough.
The trip included kayaking around the caves, swimming, pearl farm visit, fishing village, and the opportunity to climb one of the hills.
I have absolutely no hesitation in recommending Galaxy Cruise to you, particularly if you have Dwon and/or Hoan as your guide. I also suggest you do the two night cruise as we saw so much more of the Bay; and the Kayaking on the second day was even better than the first.
