Au Co cruise
Jun 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
My wife and I booked the Au Co cruise, even though it was a bit more expensive than what we were looking to pay, we decided to splurge. As has been reported, many people book the regular Baya Classic and are upgraded to the new boat for free. This seems like it would be ideal due to how expensive it is if you book online. I must say, we had a blast, the boat and esp the crew were just fantastic. At one point one of the guests was having a hard time getting back to the boat due to being tired (and over weight) and two of the crew thought he was in trouble and actually jumped into the water with their clothes on the help him. That is how dedicated they are. The boat is by far the largest in the bay compared with the other cruises. They kept us busy with very fun things to do (kayaking, biking, swimming, cave exploring). Make sure you do the Cat Ba bike ride, very neat to ride through the simple Vietnamese villiage and good exercise. Overall, just a great experience and we are very glad we chose Au Co. The Captain is really funny Aussy too!
